aiobungie.rest

Implementation of a RESTful client for Bungie's REST API.

This client only makes HTTP requests to the API and returns pure JSON objects.

 116"""The trace logging level for the `RESTClient` responses.

 134def _collect_components(components: list[enums.ComponentType], /) -> str:
 135    pending: list[str] = []
 136
 137    for component in components:
 138        if isinstance(component.value, tuple):
 139            pending.extend(str(c) for c in component.value)  # type: ignore
 140        else:
 141            pending.append(str(component.value))
 142    return ",".join(pending)

 145def _uuid() -> str:
 146    return uuid.uuid4().hex

 149def _ensure_manifest_language(language: str) -> None:
 150    langs = "\n".join(_MANIFEST_LANGUAGES)
 151    if language not in _MANIFEST_LANGUAGES:
 152        raise ValueError(
 153            f"{language} is not a valid manifest language, "
 154            f"valid languages are: {langs}"
 155        )

 158def _write_json_bytes(data: bytes) -> None:
 159    import json
 160
 161    with open("manifest.json", "wb") as file:
 162        file.write(json.dumps(json.loads(data), indent=4).encode("utf-8"))
 163
 164
 165def _write_sqlite_bytes(data: bytes, file_name: str = "manifest.sqlite3") -> None:
 166    try:
 167        with open(f"{_uuid()}.zip", "wb") as tmp:
 168            tmp.write(data)
 169
 170        with zipfile.ZipFile(tmp.name) as zipped:
 171            file = zipped.namelist()
 172
 173            if file:
 174                zipped.extractall(".")
 175
 176            os.rename(file[0], file_name)
 177            _LOG.debug("Finished downloading manifest.")
 178
 179    finally:
 180        pathlib.Path(tmp.name).unlink(missing_ok=True)

 183class _Session:
 184
 185    __slots__ = ("client_session",)
 186
 187    def __init__(self, client_session: aiohttp.ClientSession) -> None:
 188        self.client_session = client_session
 189
 190    @classmethod
 191    def acquire_session(
 192        cls,
 193        *,
 194        owner: bool = False,
 195        raise_status: bool = False,
 196        total_timeout: typing.Optional[float] = 30,
 197        connect: typing.Optional[float] = None,
 198        socket_read: typing.Optional[float] = None,
 199        socket_connect: typing.Optional[float] = None,
 200        **kwargs: typing.Any,
 201    ) -> _Session:
 202        """Creates a new TCP connection client session."""
 203        session = aiohttp.ClientSession(
 204            connector=aiohttp.TCPConnector(ssl=False, **kwargs),
 205            connector_owner=owner,
 206            raise_for_status=raise_status,
 207            timeout=aiohttp.ClientTimeout(
 208                total=total_timeout,
 209                sock_read=socket_read,
 210                sock_connect=socket_connect,
 211                connect=connect,
 212            ),
 213        )
 214        _LOG.debug("Acquired new session.")
 215        return _Session(client_session=session)
 216
 217    async def close(self) -> None:
 218        # Close the TCP connector and all sessions.
 219        _LOG.debug("Closing connections...")
 220        if self.client_session.connector is not None:
 221            # await self.client_session.connector.close()
 222            await self.client_session.connector.close()
 223            await asyncio.sleep(0.025)
 224            _LOG.debug("All connections has been closed.")

 246class RESTPool:
 247    """Pool of `RESTClient` instances.
 248
 249    This allows to create multiple instances of `RESTClient`s that can be acquired
 250    which share the same connector and metadata.
 251
 252    Example
 253    -------
 254    ```py
 255    import aiobungie
 256
 257    client_pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token", client_id=1234, client_secret='secret')
 258
 259    # Using a context manager to acquire an instance
 260    # of the pool and close the connection after finishing.
 261
 262    async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
 263        await client.download_manifest()
 264        return client.build_oauth2_url()
 265
 266    # Other people may acquire an instance from the pool.
 267    async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
 268        new_tokens = await client.refresh_access_token("token")
 269
 270        # Tokens now can be used from any pool.
 271        client.metadata['tokens'] = new_tokens
 272    ```
 273
 274    Parameters
 275    ----------
 276    token : `str`
 277        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
 278
 279    Other Parameters
 280    ----------------
 281    max_retries : `int`
 282        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
 283    max_ratelimit_retries : `int`
 284        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `429` status code. Defaults to `3`.
 285    client_secret : `typing.Optional[str]`
 286        An optional application client secret,
 287        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 288    client_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
 289        An optional application client id,
 290        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 291    enable_debugging : `bool | str`
 292        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
 293
 294    Logging Levels
 295    --------------
 296    * `False`: This will disable logging.
 297    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
 298    Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
 299    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
 300    """
 301
 302    __slots__ = (
 303        "_token",
 304        "_max_retries",
 305        "_client_secret",
 306        "_client_id",
 307        "_max_rate_limit_retries",
 308        "_metadata",
 309        "_enable_debug",
 310    )
 311
 312    # Looks like mypy doesn't like this.
 313    if typing.TYPE_CHECKING:
 314        _enable_debug: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int]
 315
 316    def __init__(
 317        self,
 318        token: str,
 319        /,
 320        client_secret: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 321        client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None,
 322        *,
 323        max_retries: int = 4,
 324        max_rate_limit_retries: int = 3,
 325        enable_debugging: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
 326    ) -> None:
 327        self._client_secret = client_secret
 328        self._client_id = client_id
 329        self._token: str = token
 330        self._max_retries = max_retries
 331        self._max_rate_limit_retries = max_rate_limit_retries
 332        self._metadata: collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any] = {}
 333        self._enable_debug = enable_debugging
 334
 335    @property
 336    def client_id(self) -> typing.Optional[int]:
 337        return self._client_id
 338
 339    @property
 340    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
 341        """Metadata dictionary."""
 342        return self._metadata
 343
 344    @typing.final
 345    def acquire(self) -> RESTClient:
 346        """Acquires a new `RESTClient` instance from this REST pool.
 347
 348        Returns
 349        -------
 350        `RESTClient`
 351            An instance of a REST client.
 352        """
 353        instance = RESTClient(
 354            self._token,
 355            client_secret=self._client_secret,
 356            client_id=self._client_id,
 357            max_retries=self._max_retries,
 358            max_ratelimit_retries=self._max_rate_limit_retries,
 359            enable_debugging=self._enable_debug,
 360        )
 361        instance._metadata = self._metadata  # type: ignore
 362        return instance

 365class RESTClient(interfaces.RESTInterface):
 366    """A RESTful client implementation for Bungie's API.
 367
 368    This client is designed to only make HTTP requests and return JSON objects
 369    to provide RESTful functionality.
 370
 371    This client is also used within `aiobungie.Client` which deserialize those returned JSON objects
 372    using the factory into Pythonic data classes objects which provide Python functionality.
 373
 374    Example
 375    -------
 376    ```py
 377    import aiobungie
 378
 379    async def main():
 380        async with aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN") as rest_client:
 381            req = await rest_client.fetch_clan_members(4389205)
 382            clan_members = req['results']
 383            for member in clan_members:
 384                for k, v in member['destinyUserInfo'].items():
 385                    print(k, v)
 386    ```
 387
 388    Parameters
 389    ----------
 390    token : `str`
 391        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
 392
 393    Other Parameters
 394    ----------------
 395    max_retries : `int`
 396        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
 397    max_ratelimit_retries : `int`
 398        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `429` status code. Defaults to `3`.
 399    client_secret : `typing.Optional[str]`
 400        An optional application client secret,
 401        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 402    client_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
 403        An optional application client id,
 404        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 405    enable_debugging : `bool | str`
 406        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
 407
 408    Logging Levels
 409    --------------
 410    * `False`: This will disable logging.
 411    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
 412    Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
 413    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
 414    """
 415
 416    __slots__ = (
 417        "_token",
 418        "_session",
 419        "_lock",
 420        "_max_retries",
 421        "_client_secret",
 422        "_client_id",
 423        "_metadata",
 424        "_max_rate_limit_retries",
 425    )
 426
 427    def __init__(
 428        self,
 429        token: str,
 430        /,
 431        client_secret: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 432        client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None,
 433        *,
 434        max_retries: int = 4,
 435        max_ratelimit_retries: int = 3,
 436        enable_debugging: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
 437    ) -> None:
 438        self._session: typing.Optional[_Session] = None
 439        self._lock: typing.Optional[asyncio.Lock] = None
 440        self._client_secret = client_secret
 441        self._client_id = client_id
 442        self._token: str = token
 443        self._max_retries = max_retries
 444        self._max_rate_limit_retries = max_ratelimit_retries
 445        self._metadata: collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any] = {}
 446
 447        self._set_debug_level(enable_debugging)
 448
 449    @property
 450    def client_id(self) -> typing.Optional[int]:
 451        return self._client_id
 452
 453    @property
 454    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
 455        return self._metadata
 456
 457    @property
 458    def is_alive(self) -> bool:
 459        return self._session is not None
 460
 461    @typing.final
 462    def _acquire(self) -> _Session:
 463        """Acquire a AIOHTTP Client session for this REST client.
 464
 465        This is means to used internally by the client.
 466        """
 467        asyncio.get_running_loop()
 468        if self._session is None:
 469            self._session = _Session.acquire_session(
 470                owner=False,
 471                raise_status=False,
 472                connect=None,
 473                socket_read=None,
 474                socket_connect=None,
 475            )
 476        return self._session
 477
 478    @typing.final
 479    async def close(self) -> None:
 480        if self._session is not None:
 481            await self._session.close()
 482            self._session = None
 483
 484    @staticmethod
 485    def _set_debug_level(
 486        level: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
 487        file: typing.Optional[typing.Union[pathlib.Path, str]] = None,
 488    ) -> None:
 489
 490        file_handler = logging.FileHandler(file, mode="w") if file else None
 491        if level == "TRACE" or level == TRACE:
 492            logging.basicConfig(
 493                level=TRACE, handlers=[file_handler] if file_handler else None
 494            )
 495
 496        elif level:
 497            logging.basicConfig(
 498                level=logging.DEBUG, handlers=[file_handler] if file_handler else None
 499            )
 500
 501    def enable_debugging(
 502        self,
 503        level: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
 504        file: typing.Optional[typing.Union[pathlib.Path, str]] = None,
 505        /,
 506    ) -> None:
 507        self._set_debug_level(level, file)
 508
 509    @typing.final
 510    async def _request(
 511        self,
 512        method: typing.Union[RequestMethod, str],
 513        route: str,
 514        *,
 515        base: bool = False,
 516        oauth2: bool = False,
 517        auth: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 518        unwrapping: typing.Literal["json", "read"] = "json",
 519        json: typing.Optional[dict[str, typing.Any]] = None,
 520        headers: typing.Optional[dict[str, typing.Any]] = None,
 521        data: typing.Optional[typing.Union[str, dict[str, typing.Any]]] = None,
 522    ) -> typing.Any:
 523
 524        retries: int = 0
 525        session = self._acquire()
 526        headers = headers or {}
 527
 528        headers.setdefault(_USER_AGENT_HEADERS, _USER_AGENT)
 529        headers["X-API-KEY"] = self._token
 530
 531        if auth is not None:
 532            headers[_AUTH_HEADER] = f"Bearer {auth}"
 533
 534        # Handling endpoints
 535        endpoint = url.BASE
 536
 537        if not base:
 538            endpoint = endpoint + url.REST_EP
 539
 540        if oauth2:
 541            headers["Content-Type"] = "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
 542            endpoint = endpoint + url.TOKEN_EP
 543
 544        if self._lock is None:
 545            self._lock = asyncio.Lock()
 546
 547        while True:
 548            try:
 549                async with (stack := contextlib.AsyncExitStack()):
 550                    await stack.enter_async_context(self._lock)
 551
 552                    # We make the request here.
 553                    taken_time = time.monotonic()
 554                    response = await stack.enter_async_context(
 555                        session.client_session.request(
 556                            method=method,
 557                            url=f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 558                            json=json,
 559                            headers=headers,
 560                            data=data,
 561                        )
 562                    )
 563                    response_time = (time.monotonic() - taken_time) * 1_000
 564
 565                    _LOG.debug(
 566                        "%s %s %s Time %.4fms",
 567                        method,
 568                        f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 569                        f"{response.status} {response.reason}",
 570                        response_time,
 571                    )
 572
 573                    await self._handle_ratelimit(
 574                        response, method, route, self._max_rate_limit_retries
 575                    )
 576
 577                    if response.status == http.HTTPStatus.NO_CONTENT:
 578                        return None
 579
 580                    if 300 > response.status >= 200:
 581                        if unwrapping == "read":
 582                            # We need to read the bytes for the manifest response.
 583                            return await response.read()
 584
 585                        if response.content_type == _APP_JSON:
 586                            json_data = await response.json()
 587
 588                            _LOG.debug(
 589                                "%s %s %s Time %.4fms",
 590                                method,
 591                                f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 592                                f"{response.status} {response.reason}",
 593                                response_time,
 594                            )
 595
 596                            if _LOG.isEnabledFor(TRACE):
 597                                headers.update(response.headers)
 598
 599                                _LOG.log(
 600                                    TRACE,
 601                                    "%s",
 602                                    error.stringify_http_message(headers),
 603                                )
 604
 605                            # Return the response.
 606                            # oauth2 responses are not packed inside a Response object.
 607                            if oauth2:
 608                                return json_data
 609
 610                            return json_data["Response"]
 611
 612                    if (
 613                        response.status in _RETRY_5XX
 614                        and retries < self._max_retries  # noqa: W503
 615                    ):
 616                        backoff_ = backoff.ExponentialBackOff(maximum=6)
 617                        sleep_time = next(backoff_)
 618                        _LOG.warning(
 619                            "Got %i - %s. Sleeping for %.2f seconds. Remaining retries: %i",
 620                            response.status,
 621                            response.reason,
 622                            sleep_time,
 623                            self._max_retries - retries,
 624                        )
 625
 626                        retries += 1
 627                        await asyncio.sleep(sleep_time)
 628                        continue
 629
 630                    raise await error.raise_error(response)
 631            # eol
 632            except _Dyn:
 633                continue
 634

 663    # We don't want this to be super complicated.
 664    @staticmethod
 665    @typing.final
 666    async def _handle_ratelimit(
 667        response: aiohttp.ClientResponse,
 668        method: str,
 669        route: str,
 670        max_ratelimit_retries: int = 3,
 671    ) -> None:
 672
 673        if response.status != http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS:
 674            return
 675
 676        if response.content_type != _APP_JSON:
 677            raise error.HTTPError(
 678                f"Being ratelimited on non JSON request, {response.content_type}.",
 679                http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS,
 680            )
 681
 682        count: int = 0
 683        json: typedefs.JSONObject = await response.json()
 684        retry_after = float(json["ThrottleSeconds"])
 685
 686        while True:
 687            if count == max_ratelimit_retries:
 688                raise _Dyn
 689
 690            if retry_after <= 0:
 691                # We sleep for a little bit to avoid funky behavior.
 692                sleep_time = float(random.random() + 0.93) / 2
 693
 694                _LOG.warning(
 695                    "We're being ratelimited with method %s route %s. Sleeping for %.2fs.",
 696                    method,
 697                    route,
 698                    sleep_time,
 699                )
 700                count += 1
 701                await asyncio.sleep(sleep_time)
 702                continue
 703
 704            raise error.RateLimitedError(
 705                body=json,
 706                url=str(response.real_url),
 707                retry_after=retry_after,
 708            )

 722    def build_oauth2_url(
 723        self, client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None
 724    ) -> typing.Optional[str]:
 725        client_id = client_id or self._client_id
 726        if client_id is None:
 727            return None
 728
 729        return url.OAUTH2_EP_BUILDER.format(
 730            oauth_endpoint=url.OAUTH_EP,
 731            client_id=client_id,
 732            uuid=_uuid(),
 733        )

 735    async def fetch_oauth2_tokens(self, code: str, /) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 736
 737        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
 738            raise TypeError(
 739                f"Expected (int) for client id but got {type(self._client_id).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 740            )
 741
 742        if not isinstance(self._client_secret, str):
 743            raise TypeError(
 744                f"Expected (str) for client secret but got {type(self._client_secret).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 745            )
 746
 747        headers = {
 748            "client_secret": self._client_secret,
 749        }
 750
 751        data = (
 752            f"grant_type=authorization_code&code={code}"
 753            f"&client_id={self._client_id}&client_secret={self._client_secret}"
 754        )
 755
 756        response = await self._request(
 757            RequestMethod.POST, "", headers=headers, data=data, oauth2=True
 758        )
 759        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)

 761    async def refresh_access_token(
 762        self, refresh_token: str, /
 763    ) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 764        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
 765            raise TypeError(
 766                f"Expected (int) for client id but got {type(self._client_id).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 767            )
 768
 769        if not isinstance(self._client_secret, str):
 770            raise TypeError(
 771                f"Expected (str) for client secret but got {type(self._client_secret).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 772            )
 773
 774        data = {
 775            "grant_type": "refresh_token",
 776            "refresh_token": refresh_token,
 777            "client_id": self._client_id,

 779            "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
 780        }
 781
 782        response = await self._request(RequestMethod.POST, "", data=data, oauth2=True)
 783        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)

 366class RESTClient(interfaces.RESTInterface):
 367    """A RESTful client implementation for Bungie's API.
 368
 369    This client is designed to only make HTTP requests and return JSON objects
 370    to provide RESTful functionality.
 371
 372    This client is also used within `aiobungie.Client` which deserialize those returned JSON objects
 373    using the factory into Pythonic data classes objects which provide Python functionality.
 374
 375    Example
 376    -------
 377    ```py
 378    import aiobungie
 379
 380    async def main():
 381        async with aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN") as rest_client:
 382            req = await rest_client.fetch_clan_members(4389205)
 383            clan_members = req['results']
 384            for member in clan_members:
 385                for k, v in member['destinyUserInfo'].items():
 386                    print(k, v)
 387    ```
 388
 389    Parameters
 390    ----------
 391    token : `str`
 392        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
 393
 394    Other Parameters
 395    ----------------
 396    max_retries : `int`
 397        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
 398    max_ratelimit_retries : `int`
 399        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `429` status code. Defaults to `3`.
 400    client_secret : `typing.Optional[str]`
 401        An optional application client secret,
 402        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 403    client_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
 404        An optional application client id,
 405        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 406    enable_debugging : `bool | str`
 407        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
 408
 409    Logging Levels
 410    --------------
 411    * `False`: This will disable logging.
 412    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
 413    Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
 414    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
 415    """
 416
 417    __slots__ = (
 418        "_token",
 419        "_session",
 420        "_lock",
 421        "_max_retries",
 422        "_client_secret",
 423        "_client_id",
 424        "_metadata",
 425        "_max_rate_limit_retries",
 426    )

 463    def _acquire(self) -> _Session:
 464        """Acquire a AIOHTTP Client session for this REST client.
 465
 466        This is means to used internally by the client.

 510    @typing.final
 511    async def _request(
 512        self,
 513        method: typing.Union[RequestMethod, str],
 514        route: str,
 515        *,
 516        base: bool = False,
 517        oauth2: bool = False,
 518        auth: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 519        unwrapping: typing.Literal["json", "read"] = "json",
 520        json: typing.Optional[dict[str, typing.Any]] = None,
 521        headers: typing.Optional[dict[str, typing.Any]] = None,
 522        data: typing.Optional[typing.Union[str, dict[str, typing.Any]]] = None,
 523    ) -> typing.Any:
 524
 525        retries: int = 0
 526        session = self._acquire()
 527        headers = headers or {}
 528
 529        headers.setdefault(_USER_AGENT_HEADERS, _USER_AGENT)
 530        headers["X-API-KEY"] = self._token
 531
 532        if auth is not None:
 533            headers[_AUTH_HEADER] = f"Bearer {auth}"
 534
 535        # Handling endpoints
 536        endpoint = url.BASE
 537
 538        if not base:
 539            endpoint = endpoint + url.REST_EP
 540
 541        if oauth2:
 542            headers["Content-Type"] = "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
 543            endpoint = endpoint + url.TOKEN_EP
 544
 545        if self._lock is None:
 546            self._lock = asyncio.Lock()
 547
 548        while True:
 549            try:
 550                async with (stack := contextlib.AsyncExitStack()):
 551                    await stack.enter_async_context(self._lock)
 552
 553                    # We make the request here.
 554                    taken_time = time.monotonic()
 555                    response = await stack.enter_async_context(
 556                        session.client_session.request(
 557                            method=method,
 558                            url=f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 559                            json=json,
 560                            headers=headers,
 561                            data=data,
 562                        )
 563                    )
 564                    response_time = (time.monotonic() - taken_time) * 1_000
 565
 566                    _LOG.debug(
 567                        "%s %s %s Time %.4fms",
 568                        method,
 569                        f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 570                        f"{response.status} {response.reason}",
 571                        response_time,
 572                    )
 573
 574                    await self._handle_ratelimit(
 575                        response, method, route, self._max_rate_limit_retries
 576                    )
 577
 578                    if response.status == http.HTTPStatus.NO_CONTENT:
 579                        return None
 580
 581                    if 300 > response.status >= 200:
 582                        if unwrapping == "read":
 583                            # We need to read the bytes for the manifest response.
 584                            return await response.read()
 585
 586                        if response.content_type == _APP_JSON:
 587                            json_data = await response.json()
 588
 589                            _LOG.debug(
 590                                "%s %s %s Time %.4fms",
 591                                method,
 592                                f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 593                                f"{response.status} {response.reason}",
 594                                response_time,
 595                            )
 596
 597                            if _LOG.isEnabledFor(TRACE):
 598                                headers.update(response.headers)
 599
 600                                _LOG.log(
 601                                    TRACE,
 602                                    "%s",
 603                                    error.stringify_http_message(headers),
 604                                )
 605
 606                            # Return the response.
 607                            # oauth2 responses are not packed inside a Response object.
 608                            if oauth2:
 609                                return json_data
 610
 611                            return json_data["Response"]
 612
 613                    if (
 614                        response.status in _RETRY_5XX
 615                        and retries < self._max_retries  # noqa: W503
 616                    ):
 617                        backoff_ = backoff.ExponentialBackOff(maximum=6)
 618                        sleep_time = next(backoff_)
 619                        _LOG.warning(
 620                            "Got %i - %s. Sleeping for %.2f seconds. Remaining retries: %i",
 621                            response.status,
 622                            response.reason,
 623                            sleep_time,
 624                            self._max_retries - retries,
 625                        )
 626
 627                        retries += 1
 628                        await asyncio.sleep(sleep_time)
 629                        continue
 630
 631                    raise await error.raise_error(response)
 632            # eol
 633            except _Dyn:
 634                continue

 664    # We don't want this to be super complicated.
 665    @staticmethod
 666    @typing.final
 667    async def _handle_ratelimit(
 668        response: aiohttp.ClientResponse,
 669        method: str,
 670        route: str,
 671        max_ratelimit_retries: int = 3,
 672    ) -> None:
 673
 674        if response.status != http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS:
 675            return
 676
 677        if response.content_type != _APP_JSON:
 678            raise error.HTTPError(
 679                f"Being ratelimited on non JSON request, {response.content_type}.",
 680                http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS,
 681            )
 682
 683        count: int = 0
 684        json: typedefs.JSONObject = await response.json()
 685        retry_after = float(json["ThrottleSeconds"])
 686
 687        while True:
 688            if count == max_ratelimit_retries:
 689                raise _Dyn
 690
 691            if retry_after <= 0:
 692                # We sleep for a little bit to avoid funky behavior.
 693                sleep_time = float(random.random() + 0.93) / 2
 694
 695                _LOG.warning(
 696                    "We're being ratelimited with method %s route %s. Sleeping for %.2fs.",
 697                    method,
 698                    route,
 699                    sleep_time,
 700                )
 701                count += 1
 702                await asyncio.sleep(sleep_time)
 703                continue
 704
 705            raise error.RateLimitedError(
 706                body=json,
 707                url=str(response.real_url),
 708                retry_after=retry_after,
 709            )
 710

 722    @typing.final
 723    def build_oauth2_url(
 724        self, client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None
 725    ) -> typing.Optional[str]:
 726        client_id = client_id or self._client_id
 727        if client_id is None:
 728            return None
 729
 730        return url.OAUTH2_EP_BUILDER.format(
 731            oauth_endpoint=url.OAUTH_EP,
 732            client_id=client_id,
 733            uuid=_uuid(),
 734        )

 736    async def fetch_oauth2_tokens(self, code: str, /) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 737
 738        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
 739            raise TypeError(
 740                f"Expected (int) for client id but got {type(self._client_id).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 741            )
 742
 743        if not isinstance(self._client_secret, str):
 744            raise TypeError(
 745                f"Expected (str) for client secret but got {type(self._client_secret).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 746            )
 747
 748        headers = {
 749            "client_secret": self._client_secret,
 750        }
 751
 752        data = (
 753            f"grant_type=authorization_code&code={code}"
 754            f"&client_id={self._client_id}&client_secret={self._client_secret}"
 755        )
 756
 757        response = await self._request(
 758            RequestMethod.POST, "", headers=headers, data=data, oauth2=True
 759        )
 760        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)

 762    async def refresh_access_token(
 763        self, refresh_token: str, /
 764    ) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 765        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
 766            raise TypeError(
 767                f"Expected (int) for client id but got {type(self._client_id).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 768            )
 769
 770        if not isinstance(self._client_secret, str):
 771            raise TypeError(
 772                f"Expected (str) for client secret but got {type(self._client_secret).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 773            )
 774
 775        data = {
 776            "grant_type": "refresh_token",
 777            "refresh_token": refresh_token,
 778            "client_id": self._client_id,

 781        }

A RESTful client implementation for Bungie's API.

This client is designed to only make HTTP requests and return JSON objects to provide RESTful functionality.

This client is also used within aiobungie.Client which deserialize those returned JSON objects using the factory into Pythonic data classes objects which provide Python functionality.

Example
import aiobungie

async def main():
    async with aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN") as rest_client:
        req = await rest_client.fetch_clan_members(4389205)
        clan_members = req['results']
        for member in clan_members:
            for k, v in member['destinyUserInfo'].items():
                print(k, v)
Parameters
  • token (str): A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
Other Parameters
  • max_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 5xx status code.
  • max_ratelimit_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 429 status code. Defaults to 3.
  • client_secret (typing.Optional[str]): An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • client_id (typing.Optional[int]): An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • enable_debugging (bool | str): Whether to enable logging responses or not.
Logging Levels
  • False: This will disable logging.
  • True: This will set the level to DEBUG and enable logging minimal information. Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
  • "TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.

import aiobungie

247class RESTPool:
248    """Pool of `RESTClient` instances.
249
250    This allows to create multiple instances of `RESTClient`s that can be acquired
251    which share the same connector and metadata.
252
253    Example
254    -------
255    ```py
256    import aiobungie
257
258    client_pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token", client_id=1234, client_secret='secret')
259
260    # Using a context manager to acquire an instance
261    # of the pool and close the connection after finishing.
262
263    async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
264        await client.download_manifest()
265        return client.build_oauth2_url()
266
267    # Other people may acquire an instance from the pool.
268    async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
269        new_tokens = await client.refresh_access_token("token")
270
271        # Tokens now can be used from any pool.
272        client.metadata['tokens'] = new_tokens
273    ```
274
275    Parameters
276    ----------
277    token : `str`
278        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
279
280    Other Parameters
281    ----------------
282    max_retries : `int`
283        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
284    max_ratelimit_retries : `int`
285        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `429` status code. Defaults to `3`.
286    client_secret : `typing.Optional[str]`
287        An optional application client secret,
288        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
289    client_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
290        An optional application client id,
291        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
292    enable_debugging : `bool | str`
293        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
294
295    Logging Levels
296    --------------
297    * `False`: This will disable logging.
298    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
299    Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
300    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
301    """

Pool of RESTClient instances.

This allows to create multiple instances of RESTClients that can be acquired which share the same connector and metadata.

Example
import aiobungie

client_pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token", client_id=1234, client_secret='secret')

# Using a context manager to acquire an instance
# of the pool and close the connection after finishing.

async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
    await client.download_manifest()
    return client.build_oauth2_url()

# Other people may acquire an instance from the pool.
async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
    new_tokens = await client.refresh_access_token("token")

    # Tokens now can be used from any pool.
    client.metadata['tokens'] = new_tokens

  • token (str): A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
Other Parameters

  • max_ratelimit_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 429 status code. Defaults to 3.
  • client_secret (typing.Optional[str]): An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • client_id (typing.Optional[int]): An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • enable_debugging (bool | str): Whether to enable logging responses or not.
Logging Levels
  • False: This will disable logging.
  • True: This will set the level to DEBUG and enable logging minimal information. Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
  • "TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.

#   TRACE: Final[int] = 5

The trace logging level for the RESTClient responses.

You can enable this with the following code

>>> import logging
>>> logging.getLogger("aiobungie.rest").setLevel(aiobungie.TRACE)
<h1 id="or">or</h1>

>>> logging.basicConfig(level=aiobungie.TRACE)
<h1 id="or-2">Or</h1>

>>> client = aiobungie.RESTClient(..., enable_debug="TRACE")
<h1 id="or-if-youre-using-aiobungieclient">Or if you're using <code>aiobungie.Client</code></h1>

>>> client = aiobungie.Client(...)
>>> client.rest.enable_debugging(level=aiobungie.TRACE, file="rest_logs.txt") # optional file
